Rating: 3
I liked the combination of flavors but wanted to make a luncheon salad so I diced the cuke and apple, blended with a can of smoked salmon (about 8 oz.), 3 thinly sliced scallions, juice from half a lemon and a good dollop of mayo. I added in about 1/2 t of the caraway seeds, and a grind or two of pepper. I plated the sald with the watercress underneath and sprinkled the top with the remaining 1/2 t of seeds. Nice change from tuna fish.

